unity,” he said. How my mother saw my future – TerryTheVoice(Opens in a new browser tab) The festival, which is designed to showcase the rich and diverse cultures of African countries through live performances, arts, crafts, African cuisine, African fashion and African music has become one of the biggest platforms for many African rising music stars in the US. Vanguard Nigerian international musician Chidozie Okoro, professionally called ‘Mc Chido’ returns with celebrated highlife singer Pardon C on a brand new music – ‘Ogogoro’. July 17, 2018 In "Entertainment" For four days, June 4 to June 7, 2014, the city of Lagos will be treated to an unforgettable experience as Taruwa Festival of Performing Arts in Nigeria [TAF] returns with a second edition themed ‘Telling Our Stories’ May 25, 2014 In "The Arts" The enviable place of Fela Anikulakpo Kuti as one of world’s notable music legends was re-asserted last Sunday, when Jamaican legendary reggae star, Don Carlos, leading local and foreign artistes, closed this year’s edition of the annual musical concert tagged “Felabration”. October 25, 2014 In "Showtime People"